
OS level network configuration

ehternet card
		
	

		IP ADDRESS
	=============================

IP = internet protocol
	ip is equal to address for your house

		192.168.145.80  address for one machine
	s/o, xxxx, house number 2, 2n street,area name,city,state-pin 560036 or 516108

			IP CLASSES
		=====================
	Class  A    = network  - computers
	Class  B   = Network - computers
	Class  C   = Network - computers
	Class  D   = multi casting network ( tv channels, live streaming)
	Class  E    = r & d ( research and dev) network

		1  to 255
ip 1 to 255

	IBM = 10 lakhs
	Accenture = 15 lakhs employess
how we can allocate 15 lakhs ips for all employees

		1.1.1.1
		1.1.1.2
		1.1.1.3
		1.1.1.255  
	
	255 * 255 * 255 * 255
				8       8         8       8      = 32 bits
		IP  V4  = 32 bits     oct1 . oct2. oct3 . oct4
		IP  V6 = 128 bits   
	
		IPV4 = 192.168.145.1
		IPV6 = 11345ABC.2342DE3D.156ABE7E.88567EG7


			IANA = Internet Assigned number authority

	1 -255
	IANA team created or catogoriged IP to public and privite



		1 -255

		public = internet
		private = personal,with in company network

								private     			Public		
			A CLASS = 1 - 126				10.*.*.*			1-9 and 11-126.*.*.*
								1*255*255*255
				127 is reserved for loop back  	
			B CLASS = 128 - 191			172.16.*.* - 172.31.*.*        	128-172 and 173 to 191
							1*15*255*255
			C CLASS =  192 - 223			192.168.*.*
								1*1*255*255
			D CLASS = 224 - 239		15*255*255*255	
			E CLASS = 240 - 255



	10.1.1.2   is it private or public?  private
	2.1.1.2  is it private or public?  public
	172.1.1.4  is it private or public? public


	Netmask values for network classes
	   network	netmask
	10.*.*.*		255.0.0.0
	172.16.*.*	255.255.0.0
	192.168.*.*         	255.255.255.0

umask is for permissions
netmask is for network IP address


